{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WJgSk3EcZRWvMpYPupTozj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collection;\n     7→\n     8→@Entity\n     9→@Inheritance(strategy = InheritanceType.SINGLE_TABLE)\n    10→@DiscriminatorColumn(name = \"LEAGUE_TYPE\")\n    11→public abstract class League implements Serializable {\n    12→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    13→\n    14→    @Id\n    15→    protected String id;\n    16→    protected String name;\n    17→    protected String sport;\n    18→    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"league\")\n    19→    protected Collection<Team> teams = new ArrayList<>();\n    20→\n    21→    public League() {\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    public League(String id, String name, String sport) {\n    25→        this.id = id;\n    26→        this.name = name;\n    27→        this.sport = sport;\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    public String getId() {\n    31→        return id;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    public void setId(String id) {\n    35→        this.id = id;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    public String getName() {\n    39→        return name;\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    public void setName(String name) {\n    43→        this.name = name;\n    44→    }\n    45→\n    46→    public String getSport() {\n    47→        return sport;\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    public void setSport(String sport) {\n    51→        this.sport = sport;\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public Collection<Team> getTeams() {\n    55→        return teams;\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public void setTeams(Collection<Team> teams) {\n    59→        this.teams = teams;\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    public void addTeam(Team team) {\n    63→        this.teams.add(team);\n    64→    }\n    65→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"831f66ff-c9ae-4571-b43b-fbfb1716cdb8","uuid":"0173a99a-534e-4fce-ab92-c617c97548df"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0116kPnFaMPYGbGJzHnPxFer","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collection;\n     7→\n     8→@Entity\n     9→public class Player implements Serializable {\n    10→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    11→\n    12→    @Id\n    13→    private String id;\n    14→    private String name;\n    15→    private String position;\n    16→    private double salary;\n    17→    @ManyToMany(mappedBy = \"players\")\n    18→    private Collection<Team> teams = new ArrayList<>();\n    19→\n    20→    public Player() {\n    21→    }\n    22→\n    23→    public Player(String id, String name, String position, double salary) {\n    24→        this.id = id;\n    25→        this.name = name;\n    26→        this.position = position;\n    27→        this.salary = salary;\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    public String getId() {\n    31→        return id;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    public void setId(String id) {\n    35→        this.id = id;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    public String getName() {\n    39→        return name;\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    public void setName(String name) {\n    43→        this.name = name;\n    44→    }\n    45→\n    46→    public String getPosition() {\n    47→        return position;\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    public void setPosition(String position) {\n    51→        this.position = position;\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public double getSalary() {\n    55→        return salary;\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public void setSalary(double salary) {\n    59→        this.salary = salary;\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    public Collection<Team> getTeams() {\n    63→        return teams;\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    public void setTeams(Collection<Team> teams) {\n    67→        this.teams = teams;\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    public void addTeam(Team team) {\n    71→        this.teams.add(team);\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    public void dropTeam(Team team) {\n    75→        this.teams.remove(team);\n    76→    }\n    77→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"831f66ff-c9ae-4571-b43b-fbfb1716cdb8","uuid":"f2e2a546-73de-4586-bee2-d6de115f5001"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019TxZvQxtr8JBm94RCXmVNB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.DiscriminatorValue;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     5→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.util.IncorrectSportException;\n     6→\n     7→@Entity\n     8→@DiscriminatorValue(\"SUMMER\")\n     9→public class SummerLeague extends League {\n    10→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    11→\n    12→    public SummerLeague() {\n    13→    }\n    14→\n    15→    public SummerLeague(String id, String name, String sport) throws IncorrectSportException {\n    16→        super(id, name, sport);\n    17→        if (!sport.equalsIgnoreCase(\"soccer\") && !sport.equalsIgnoreCase(\"swimming\") &&\n    18→            !sport.equalsIgnoreCase(\"basketball\") && !sport.equalsIgnoreCase(\"baseball\")) {\n    19→            throw new IncorrectSportException(\"Sport is not a summer sport.\");\n    20→        }\n    21→    }\n    22→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"831f66ff-c9ae-4571-b43b-fbfb1716cdb8","uuid":"ba9ea578-2b42-4786-a37f-a9fc1e266438"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01V31WfxELGKdZVy1CRQEunV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collection;\n     7→\n     8→@Entity\n     9→public class Team implements Serializable {\n    10→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    11→\n    12→    @Id\n    13→    private String id;\n    14→    private String name;\n    15→    private String city;\n    16→    @ManyToMany\n    17→    private Collection<Player> players = new ArrayList<>();\n    18→    @ManyToOne\n    19→    private League league;\n    20→\n    21→    public Team() {\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    public Team(String id, String name, String city) {\n    25→        this.id = id;\n    26→        this.name = name;\n    27→        this.city = city;\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    public String getId() {\n    31→        return id;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    public void setId(String id) {\n    35→        this.id = id;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    public String getName() {\n    39→        return name;\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    public void setName(String name) {\n    43→        this.name = name;\n    44→    }\n    45→\n    46→    public String getCity() {\n    47→        return city;\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    public void setCity(String city) {\n    51→        this.city = city;\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public Collection<Player> getPlayers() {\n    55→        return players;\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public void setPlayers(Collection<Player> players) {\n    59→        this.players = players;\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    public League getLeague() {\n    63→        return league;\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    public void setLeague(League league) {\n    67→        this.league = league;\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    public void addPlayer(Player player) {\n    71→        this.players.add(player);\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    public void dropPlayer(Player player) {\n    75→        this.players.remove(player);\n    76→    }\n    77→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"831f66ff-c9ae-4571-b43b-fbfb1716cdb8","uuid":"092e1668-c180-4bf0-9282-aa97ab0306cc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HTCfNdnENA7nrPMc9xRF3U","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.DiscriminatorValue;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     5→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.util.IncorrectSportException;\n     6→\n     7→@Entity\n     8→@DiscriminatorValue(\"WINTER\")\n     9→public class WinterLeague extends League {\n    10→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    11→\n    12→    public WinterLeague() {\n    13→    }\n    14→\n    15→    public WinterLeague(String id, String name, String sport) throws IncorrectSportException {\n    16→        super(id, name, sport);\n    17→        if (!sport.equalsIgnoreCase(\"hockey\") && !sport.equalsIgnoreCase(\"skiing\") &&\n    18→            !sport.equalsIgnoreCase(\"snowboarding\")) {\n    19→            throw new IncorrectSportException(\"Sport is not a winter sport.\");\n    20→        }\n    21→    }\n    22→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"831f66ff-c9ae-4571-b43b-fbfb1716cdb8","uuid":"7d210509-c41d-4719-a65f-b03100997249"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y7MerwqChS4MyQP77LrfCz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.roster.request;\n     2→\n     3→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n     4→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n     5→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.util.PlayerDetails;\n     6→\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→\n     9→public interface Request {\n    10→    void createPlayer(String id, String name, String position, double salary);\n    11→    void addPlayer(String playerId, String teamId);\n    12→    void removePlayer(String playerId);\n    13→    void dropPlayer(String playerId, String teamId);\n    14→    PlayerDetails getPlayer(String playerId);\n    15→    List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersOfTeam(String teamId);\n    16→    List<TeamDetails> getTeamsOfLeague(String leagueId);\n    17→    List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByPosition(String position);\n    18→    List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByHigherSalary(String name);\n    19→    List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersBySalaryRange(double low, double high);\n    20→    List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByLeagueId(String leagueId);\n    21→    List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersBySport(String sport);\n    22→    List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByCity(String city);\n    23→    List<PlayerDetails> getAllPlayers();\n    24→    List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersNotOnTeam();\n    25→    List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByPositionAndName(String position, String name);\n    26→    List<LeagueDetails> getLeaguesOfPlayer(String playerId);\n    27→    List<String> getSportsOfPlayer(String playerId);\n    28→    void createTeamInLeague(TeamDetails teamDetails, String leagueId);\n    29→    void removeTeam(String teamId);\n    30→    TeamDetails getTeam(String teamId);\n    31→    void createLeague(LeagueDetails leagueDetails);\n    32→    void removeLeague(String leagueId);\n    33→    LeagueDetails getLeague(String leagueId);\n    34→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"831f66ff-c9ae-4571-b43b-fbfb1716cdb8","uuid":"59188fb9-99e1-4ca8-a17d-a63f50caaf63"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011fo9DAAY3XtrgYTo9d1wcY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.roster.request;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.TypedQuery;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaBuilder;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaQuery;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.Join;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.Predicate;\n    12→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.Root;\n    13→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity.League;\n    14→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity.League_;\n    15→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity.Player;\n    16→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity.Player_;\n    17→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity.SummerLeague;\n    18→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity.Team;\n    19→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity.Team_;\n    20→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity.WinterLeague;\n    21→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.util.IncorrectSportException;\n    22→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n    23→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.util.PlayerDetails;\n    24→import quarkus.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n    25→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    26→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    27→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    28→import jakarta.ws.rs.DELETE;\n    29→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    30→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    31→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    32→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    33→import jakarta.ws.rs.QueryParam;\n    34→import jakarta.ws.rs.WebApplicationException;\n    35→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    36→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    37→\n    38→import java.io.Serializable;\n    39→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    40→import java.util.Collection;\n    41→import java.util.List;\n    42→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    43→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    44→\n    45→@ApplicationScoped\n    46→@Path(\"/roster\")\n    47→public class RequestBean implements Request, Serializable {\n    48→    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(\"quarkus.tutorial.roster.request.RequestBean\");\n    49→\n    50→    @Inject\n    51→    private EntityManager em;\n    52→    private CriteriaBuilder cb;\n    53→\n    54→    @PostConstruct\n    55→    private void init() {\n    56→        cb = em.getCriteriaBuilder();\n    57→    }\n    58→\n    59→    @Override\n    60→    @POST\n    61→    @Path(\"/player\")\n    62→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    63→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    64→    @Transactional\n    65→    public void createPlayer(\n    66→            @FormParam(\"id\") String id,\n    67→            @FormParam(\"name\") String name,\n    68→            @FormParam(\"position\") String position,\n    69→            @FormParam(\"salary\") double salary) {\n    70→        logger.info(\"createPlayer\");\n    71→        try {\n    72→            Player player = new Player(id, name, position, salary);\n    73→            em.persist(player);\n    74→            em.flush();\n    75→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n    76→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n    77→        }\n    78→    }\n    79→\n    80→    @Override\n    81→    @POST\n    82→    @Path(\"/player/{playerId}/team/{teamId}\")\n    83→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    84→    @Transactional\n    85→    public void addPlayer(@PathParam(\"playerId\") String playerId, @PathParam(\"teamId\") String teamId) {\n    86→        logger.info(\"addPlayer\");\n    87→        try {\n    88→            Player player = em.find(Player.class, playerId);\n    89→            Team team = em.find(Team.class, teamId);\n    90→            if (player == null || team == null) {\n    91→                throw new WebApplicationException(\"Player or Team not found\", Response.Status.NOT_FOUND);\n    92→            }\n    93→            team.addPlayer(player);\n    94→            player.addTeam(team);\n    95→            em.merge(player);\n    96→            em.merge(team);\n    97→            em.flush();\n    98→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n    99→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   100→        }\n   101→    }\n   102→\n   103→    @Override\n   104→    @DELETE\n   105→    @Path(\"/player/{playerId}\")\n   106→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   107→    @Transactional\n   108→    public void removePlayer(@PathParam(\"playerId\") String playerId) {\n   109→        logger.info(\"removePlayer\");\n   110→        try {\n   111→            Player player = em.find(Player.class, playerId);\n   112→            if (player == null) {\n   113→                throw new WebApplicationException(\"Player not found\", Response.Status.NOT_FOUND);\n   114→            }\n   115→            Collection<Team> teams = player.getTeams();\n   116→            for (Team team : teams) {\n   117→                team.dropPlayer(player);\n   118→            }\n   119→            em.remove(player);\n   120→            em.flush();\n   121→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   122→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   123→        }\n   124→    }\n   125→\n   126→    @Override\n   127→    @DELETE\n   128→    @Path(\"/player/{playerId}/team/{teamId}\")\n   129→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   130→    @Transactional\n   131→    public void dropPlayer(@PathParam(\"playerId\") String playerId, @PathParam(\"teamId\") String teamId) {\n   132→        logger.info(\"dropPlayer\");\n   133→        try {\n   134→            Player player = em.find(Player.class, playerId);\n   135→            Team team = em.find(Team.class, teamId);\n   136→            if (player == null || team == null) {\n   137→                throw new WebApplicationException(\"Player or Team not found\", Response.Status.NOT_FOUND);\n   138→            }\n   139→            team.dropPlayer(player);\n   140→            player.dropTeam(team);\n   141→            em.merge(player);\n   142→            em.merge(team);\n   143→            em.flush();\n   144→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   145→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   146→        }\n   147→    }\n   148→\n   149→    @Override\n   150→    @GET\n   151→    @Path(\"/player/{playerId}\")\n   152→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   153→    public PlayerDetails getPlayer(@PathParam(\"playerId\") String playerId) {\n   154→        logger.info(\"getPlayerDetails\");\n   155→        try {\n   156→            Player player = em.find(Player.class, playerId);\n   157→            if (player == null) {\n   158→                throw new WebApplicationException(\"Player not found\", Response.Status.NOT_FOUND);\n   159→            }\n   160→            return new PlayerDetails(player.getId(), player.getName(), player.getPosition(), player.getSalary());\n   161→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   162→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   163→        }\n   164→    }\n   165→\n   166→    @Override\n   167→    @GET\n   168→    @Path(\"/team/{teamId}/players\")\n   169→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   170→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersOfTeam(@PathParam(\"teamId\") String teamId) {\n   171→        logger.info(\"getPlayersOfTeam\");\n   172→        try {\n   173→            Team team = em.find(Team.class, teamId);\n   174→            if (team == null) {\n   175→                throw new WebApplicationException(\"Team not found\", Response.Status.NOT_FOUND);\n   176→            }\n   177→            return copyPlayersToDetails((List<Player>) team.getPlayers());\n   178→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   179→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   180→        }\n   181→    }\n   182→\n   183→    @Override\n   184→    @GET\n   185→    @Path(\"/league/{leagueId}/teams\")\n   186→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   187→    public List<TeamDetails> getTeamsOfLeague(@PathParam(\"leagueId\") String leagueId) {\n   188→        logger.info(\"getTeamsOfLeague\");\n   189→        List<TeamDetails> detailsList = new ArrayList<>();\n   190→        try {\n   191→            League league = em.find(League.class, leagueId);\n   192→            if (league == null) {\n   193→                throw new WebApplicationException(\"League not found\", Response.Status.NOT_FOUND);\n   194→            }\n   195→            for (Team team : league.getTeams()) {\n   196→                detailsList.add(new TeamDetails(team.getId(), team.getName(), team.getCity()));\n   197→            }\n   198→            return detailsList;\n   199→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   200→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   201→        }\n   202→    }\n   203→\n   204→    @Override\n   205→    @GET\n   206→    @Path(\"/players/position/{position}\")\n   207→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   208→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByPosition(@PathParam(\"position\") String position) {\n   209→        logger.info(\"getPlayersByPosition\");\n   210→        try {\n   211→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   212→            Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   213→            cq.where(cb.equal(player.get(Player_.position), position));\n   214→            cq.select(player);\n   215→            TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   216→            List<Player> players = q.getResultList();\n   217→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   218→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   219→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   220→        }\n   221→    }\n   222→\n   223→    @Override\n   224→    @GET\n   225→    @Path(\"/players/salary/higher/{name}\")\n   226→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   227→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByHigherSalary(@PathParam(\"name\") String name) {\n   228→        logger.info(\"getPlayersByHigherSalary\");\n   229→        try {\n   230→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   231→            Root<Player> player1 = cq.from(Player.class);\n   232→            Root<Player> player2 = cq.from(Player.class);\n   233→            Predicate gtPredicate = cb.greaterThan(player1.get(Player_.salary), player2.get(Player_.salary));\n   234→            Predicate equalPredicate = cb.equal(player2.get(Player_.name), name);\n   235→            cq.where(gtPredicate, equalPredicate);\n   236→            cq.select(player1).distinct(true);\n   237→            TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   238→            List<Player> players = q.getResultList();\n   239→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   240→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   241→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   242→        }\n   243→    }\n   244→\n   245→    @Override\n   246→    @GET\n   247→    @Path(\"/players/salary/range\")\n   248→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   249→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersBySalaryRange(@QueryParam(\"low\") double low, @QueryParam(\"high\") double high) {\n   250→        logger.info(\"getPlayersBySalaryRange\");\n   251→        try {\n   252→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   253→            Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   254→            cq.where(cb.between(player.get(Player_.salary), low, high));\n   255→            cq.select(player).distinct(true);\n   256→            TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   257→            List<Player> players = q.getResultList();\n   258→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   259→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   260→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   261→        }\n   262→    }\n   263→\n   264→    @Override\n   265→    @GET\n   266→    @Path(\"/players/league/{leagueId}\")\n   267→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   268→    @Transactional\n   269→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByLeagueId(@PathParam(\"leagueId\") String leagueId) {\n   270→        logger.info(\"getPlayersByLeagueId\");\n   271→        try {\n   272→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   273→            Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   274→            Join<Player, Team> team = player.join(Player_.teams);\n   275→            Join<Team, League> league = team.join(Team_.league);\n   276→            cq.where(cb.equal(league.get(League_.id), leagueId));\n   277→            cq.select(player).distinct(true);\n   278→            TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   279→            List<Player> players = q.getResultList();\n   280→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   281→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   282→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   283→        }\n   284→    }\n   285→\n   286→    @Override\n   287→    @GET\n   288→    @Path(\"/players/sport/{sport}\")\n   289→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   290→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersBySport(@PathParam(\"sport\") String sport) {\n   291→        logger.info(\"getPlayersBySport\");\n   292→        try {\n   293→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   294→            Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   295→            Join<Player, Team> team = player.join(Player_.teams);\n   296→            Join<Team, League> league = team.join(Team_.league);\n   297→            cq.where(cb.equal(league.get(League_.sport), sport));\n   298→            cq.select(player).distinct(true);\n   299→            TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   300→            List<Player> players = q.getResultList();\n   301→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   302→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   303→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   304→        }\n   305→    }\n   306→\n   307→    @Override\n   308→    @GET\n   309→    @Path(\"/players/city/{city}\")\n   310→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   311→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByCity(@PathParam(\"city\") String city) {\n   312→        logger.info(\"getPlayersByCity\");\n   313→        try {\n   314→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   315→            Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   316→            Join<Player, Team> team = player.join(Player_.teams);\n   317→            cq.where(cb.equal(team.get(Team_.city), city));\n   318→            cq.select(player).distinct(true);\n   319→            TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   320→            List<Player> players = q.getResultList();\n   321→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   322→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   323→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   324→        }\n   325→    }\n   326→\n   327→    @Override\n   328→    @GET\n   329→    @Path(\"/players\")\n   330→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   331→    public List<PlayerDetails> getAllPlayers() {\n   332→        logger.info(\"getAllPlayers\");\n   333→        try {\n   334→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   335→            Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   336→            cq.select(player);\n   337→            TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   338→            List<Player> players = q.getResultList();\n   339→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   340→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   341→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   342→        }\n   343→    }\n   344→\n   345→    @Override\n   346→    @GET\n   347→    @Path(\"/players/not-on-team\")\n   348→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   349→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersNotOnTeam() {\n   350→        logger.info(\"getPlayersNotOnTeam\");\n   351→        try {\n   352→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   353→            Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   354→            cq.where(cb.isEmpty(player.get(Player_.teams)));\n   355→            cq.select(player).distinct(true);\n   356→            TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   357→            List<Player> players = q.getResultList();\n   358→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   359→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   360→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   361→        }\n   362→    }\n   363→\n   364→    @Override\n   365→    @GET\n   366→    @Path(\"/players/position/{position}/name/{name}\")\n   367→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   368→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByPositionAndName(\n   369→            @PathParam(\"position\") String position,\n   370→            @PathParam(\"name\") String name) {\n   371→        logger.info(\"getPlayersByPositionAndName\");\n   372→        try {\n   373→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   374→            Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   375→            cq.where(cb.equal(player.get(Player_.position), position),\n   376→                    cb.equal(player.get(Player_.name), name));\n   377→            cq.select(player).distinct(true);\n   378→            TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   379→            List<Player> players = q.getResultList();\n   380→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   381→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   382→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   383→        }\n   384→    }\n   385→\n   386→    @Override\n   387→    @GET\n   388→    @Path(\"/player/{playerId}/leagues\")\n   389→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   390→    public List<LeagueDetails> getLeaguesOfPlayer(@PathParam(\"playerId\") String playerId) {\n   391→        logger.info(\"getLeaguesOfPlayer\");\n   392→        List<LeagueDetails> detailsList = new ArrayList<>();\n   393→        try {\n   394→            CriteriaQuery<League> cq = cb.createQuery(League.class);\n   395→            Root<League> leagueRoot = cq.from(League.class);\n   396→            Join<League, Team> team = leagueRoot.join(League_.teams);\n   397→            Join<Team, Player> player = team.join(Team_.players);\n   398→            cq.where(cb.equal(player.get(Player_.id), playerId));\n   399→            cq.select(leagueRoot).distinct(true);\n   400→            TypedQuery<League> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   401→            List<League> leagues = q.getResultList();\n   402→            if (leagues == null || leagues.isEmpty()) {\n   403→                logger.warning(\"No leagues found for player with ID \" + playerId);\n   404→                return null;\n   405→            }\n   406→            for (League currentLeague : leagues) {\n   407→                detailsList.add(new LeagueDetails(currentLeague.getId(), currentLeague.getName(), currentLeague.getSport()));\n   408→            }\n   409→            return detailsList;\n   410→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   411→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   412→        }\n   413→    }\n   414→\n   415→    @Override\n   416→    @GET\n   417→    @Path(\"/player/{playerId}/sports\")\n   418→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   419→    public List<String> getSportsOfPlayer(@PathParam(\"playerId\") String playerId) {\n   420→        logger.info(\"getSportsOfPlayer\");\n   421→        try {\n   422→            CriteriaQuery<String> cq = cb.createQuery(String.class);\n   423→            Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   424→            Join<Player, Team> team = player.join(Player_.teams);\n   425→            Join<Team, League> league = team.join(Team_.league);\n   426→            cq.where(cb.equal(player.get(Player_.id), playerId));\n   427→            cq.select(league.get(League_.sport)).distinct(true);\n   428→            TypedQuery<String> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   429→            return q.getResultList();\n   430→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   431→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   432→        }\n   433→    }\n   434→\n   435→    @Override\n   436→    @POST\n   437→    @Path(\"/team/league/{leagueId}\")\n   438→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   439→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   440→    @Transactional\n   441→    public void createTeamInLeague(TeamDetails teamDetails, @PathParam(\"leagueId\") String leagueId) {\n   442→        logger.info(\"createTeamInLeague\");\n   443→        try {\n   444→            League league = em.find(League.class, leagueId);\n   445→            if (league == null) {\n   446→                throw new WebApplicationException(\"League not found\", Response.Status.NOT_FOUND);\n   447→            }\n   448→            Team team = new Team(teamDetails.getId(), teamDetails.getName(), teamDetails.getCity());\n   449→            em.persist(team);\n   450→            team.setLeague(league);\n   451→            league.addTeam(team);\n   452→            em.merge(league);\n   453→            em.flush();\n   454→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   455→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   456→        }\n   457→    }\n   458→\n   459→    @Override\n   460→    @DELETE\n   461→    @Path(\"/team/{teamId}\")\n   462→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   463→    @Transactional\n   464→    public void removeTeam(@PathParam(\"teamId\") String teamId) {\n   465→        logger.info(\"removeTeam\");\n   466→        try {\n   467→            Team team = em.find(Team.class, teamId);\n   468→            if (team == null) {\n   469→                throw new WebApplicationException(\"Team not found\", Response.Status.NOT_FOUND);\n   470→            }\n   471→            for (Player player : team.getPlayers()) {\n   472→                player.dropTeam(team);\n   473→                em.merge(player);\n   474→            }\n   475→            em.remove(team);\n   476→            em.flush();\n   477→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   478→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   479→        }\n   480→    }\n   481→\n   482→    @Override\n   483→    @GET\n   484→    @Path(\"/team/{teamId}\")\n   485→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   486→    public TeamDetails getTeam(@PathParam(\"teamId\") String teamId) {\n   487→        logger.info(\"getTeam\");\n   488→        try {\n   489→            Team team = em.find(Team.class, teamId);\n   490→            if (team == null) {\n   491→                throw new WebApplicationException(\"Team not found\", Response.Status.NOT_FOUND);\n   492→            }\n   493→            return new TeamDetails(team.getId(), team.getName(), team.getCity());\n   494→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   495→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   496→        }\n   497→    }\n   498→\n   499→    @Override\n   500→    @POST\n   501→    @Path(\"/league\")\n   502→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   503→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   504→    @Transactional\n   505→    public void createLeague(LeagueDetails leagueDetails) {\n   506→        logger.info(\"createLeague\");\n   507→        try {\n   508→            String sport = leagueDetails.getSport().toLowerCase();\n   509→            if (sport.equals(\"soccer\") || sport.equals(\"swimming\") || sport.equals(\"basketball\") || sport.equals(\"baseball\")) {\n   510→                SummerLeague league = new SummerLeague(leagueDetails.getId(), leagueDetails.getName(), leagueDetails.getSport());\n   511→                em.persist(league);\n   512→                em.flush();\n   513→            } else if (sport.equals(\"hockey\") || sport.equals(\"skiing\") || sport.equals(\"snowboarding\")) {\n   514→                WinterLeague league = new WinterLeague(leagueDetails.getId(), leagueDetails.getName(), leagueDetails.getSport());\n   515→                em.persist(league);\n   516→                em.flush();\n   517→            } else {\n   518→                throw new IncorrectSportException(\"The specified sport is not valid.\");\n   519→            }\n   520→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   521→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.BAD_REQUEST);\n   522→        }\n   523→    }\n   524→\n   525→    @Override\n   526→    @DELETE\n   527→    @Path(\"/league/{leagueId}\")\n   528→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   529→    @Transactional\n   530→    public void removeLeague(@PathParam(\"leagueId\") String leagueId) {\n   531→        logger.info(\"removeLeague\");\n   532→        try {\n   533→            League league = em.find(League.class, leagueId);\n   534→            if (league == null) {\n   535→                throw new WebApplicationException(\"League not found\", Response.Status.NOT_FOUND);\n   536→            }\n   537→            em.remove(league);\n   538→            em.flush();\n   539→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   540→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   541→        }\n   542→    }\n   543→\n   544→    @Override\n   545→    @GET\n   546→    @Path(\"/league/{leagueId}\")\n   547→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   548→    public LeagueDetails getLeague(@PathParam(\"leagueId\") String leagueId) {\n   549→        logger.info(\"getLeague\");\n   550→        try {\n   551→            League league = em.find(League.class, leagueId);\n   552→            if (league == null) {\n   553→                throw new WebApplicationException(\"League not found\", Response.Status.NOT_FOUND);\n   554→            }\n   555→            return new LeagueDetails(league.getId(), league.getName(), league.getSport());\n   556→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   557→            throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\n   558→        }\n   559→    }\n   560→\n   561→    private List<PlayerDetails> copyPlayersToDetails(List<Player> players) {\n   562→        List<PlayerDetails> detailsList = new ArrayList<>();\n   563→        for (Player player : players) {\n   564→            detailsList.add(new PlayerDetails(player.getId(), player.getName(), player.getPosition(), player.getSalary()));\n   565→        }\n   566→        return detailsList;\n   567→    }\n   568→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"831f66ff-c9ae-4571-b43b-fbfb1716cdb8","uuid":"5af6a74a-478f-4761-b37a-7b33d46a9c13"}
