{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LP7x2ejGnSpcgKCdc4NqCD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The DROP TABLE errors are just initial cleanup (expected with drop-and-create). The real issue is the 400/500 errors on the REST calls. The problem is likely:\n\n1. The Hibernate metamodel classes (Player_, Team_, League_) aren't compatible with EclipseLink (Open Liberty's JPA provider)\n2. The `@Transactional` on CDI beans may need different handling\n\nI need to refactor the code to:\n1. Replace Hibernate `Player_`, `Team_`, `League_` metamodel references with string-based JPA Criteria API calls, or switch to using EclipseLink-generated metamodel\n2. Use `@Stateless` EJB instead of `@ApplicationScoped` CDI bean with `@Transactional` for proper JTA transaction management\n\nLet me make these changes:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2849,"cache_read_input_tokens":109406,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2849,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":581},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"831f66ff-c9ae-4571-b43b-fbfb1716cdb8","uuid":"8ce9901a-bd0e-4f88-bf52-a81b05b611a3"}
